The paper deals with the problem of anonymous information delivery, which involves information theory, cryptography, and distributed systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves distributed storage and retrieval, which suggests cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as possible categories. Finally, the paper involves coding and communication, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible category.
